e a park after Jean Okimasis |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/saskatchewan/jean-okimasis-regina-city-park-1.4771085 |accessdate=6 March 2020 |agency=CBC News |date=August 2, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, a park was named after Okim\u0101sis in Regina.<ref name=\"CBC:Park\"/><ref name=\"CL:park\"/>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Arok Wolvengrey]]\n*[[Solomon Ratt]]\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== Bibliography ==\n* {{cite book\n |last      = Okim\u0101sis\n |first     = Jean\n |title     = Cree: Language of the Plains/n\u0113hiyaw\u0113win: paskw\u0101wi-p\u012bkiskw\u0113win\n |publisher = Canadian Plains Research Center\n |editor    = \n |url       = \n |year      = 2004\n |place     = Regina\n |isbn      = 0-88977-155-3\n}}\n* {{cite book\n |last1      = Okim\u0101sis\n |first1     = Jean\n |last2      = Wolvengrey\n |first2     = Arok\n |title     = How to Spell it in Cree (The Standard Roman Orthography)\n |publisher = miyw\u0101sin ink\n |editor    = \n |url       = https://creeliteracy.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/htsiic-covers-nocontacts.pdf\n |year      = 2009\n |place     = Regina\n |isbn      = 978-0-9784935-0-9\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://uofrpress.ca/Contributors/O/Okimasis-Jean|Jean Okim\u0101sis] on the [[University of Regina]] Press\n\n{{authority control|LCCN=nb2001048310}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:}}\n\n[[Category:1938 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Linguists from Canada]]\n[[Category:University of Regina alumni]]\n[[Category:Linguists of Algic languages]]\n\n\n{{Canada-linguist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "EddieASantos", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adjust hyperlinks", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean_Okim%C4%81sis"}
